# Merkabit Simulations

Computational validation code for:

**The Merkabit: A Ternary Computational Unit on the Eisenstein Lattice**
Selina Stenberg & Claude (Anthropic), 2026

This repository contains every simulation referenced in the paper's appendices. All scripts produce deterministic output with fixed random seeds and require only Python 3.8+ and NumPy.

---

## Scripts

| Script | Appendix | Paper Sections | What it does |
|--------|----------|----------------|--------------|
| `pentachoric_code_simulation.py` | C | 9.2, 9.5 | Static pentachoric detection on the 7-node Eisenstein cell. Exhaustive enumeration of all 5⁷ = 78,125 gate assignments × 28 error scenarios. |
| `dynamic_pentachoric_simulation.py` | C | 9.5, 9.8 | Dynamic detection with ouroboros gate rotation active. Validates the dynamic detection rates (95.1% overall, 100% central) and composite suppression (41–68×). |
| `lattice_scaling_simulation.py` | D | 9.7 | Extends detection analysis to 19-node and 37-node Eisenstein cells via Monte Carlo. Tests whether detection improves with the interior-to-boundary ratio. Provides the `EisensteinCell` class used by all lattice-based simulations. |
| `optimal_gate_assignment.py` | D | 9.7 | Minimax optimisation: finds the gate assignment that maximises the worst-case detection rate. Exhaustive on 7-node cell; simulated annealing on 19- and 37-node cells. |
| `pentachoric_decoder_simulation.py` | E | 9.7 | Majority-vote decoder baseline. Converts pentachoric closure failures into error localisation and correction. |
| `gateaware_decoder_simulation.py` | E | 9.7 | Gate-aware decoder with consistency checks, exclusion principle, and time-series validation. Improves correction fidelity by ~12 percentage points over majority-vote. |
| `e6_syndrome_decoder_simulation.py` | F | 10 | Level 3 error correction via the E₆ root system. Implements the full decoding pipeline: sector identification → root direction → correction gate. |
| `noise_model_decomposition.py` | G | 10.10.1 | Decomposes platform-specific noise (superconducting, photonic, trapped ion) into the 7 syndrome sectors of the P₂₄ representation ring. Three-level composite suppression analysis. |
| `threshold_sweep_simulation.py` | H | 9.7, 10.10.4 | Fault-tolerance threshold identification. Sweeps raw error rate from 10⁻¹ to 10⁻⁴ across cell sizes to find the crossing point where scaling helps. |
| `pf_gate_simulation.py` | I | 8.1–8.2 | Verification of the P and F gates — the two single-merkabit gates with no qubit analogue. Tests unitarity, ternary navigation, frequency–phase duality, commutation relations, ouroboros period-12, and the state-space reachability proof. |
| `native_algorithm_benchmarks.py` | J | 8.9.5 | Gate-cost benchmarks comparing merkabit vs qubit across five problem classes: ternary search, long-range coupling, graph colouring, reversible computation, and zero-state controlled operations. |

