## Running

Each script runs independently and prints results to stdout:

```bash
python3 lattice_scaling_simulation.py
python3 optimal_gate_assignment.py
python3 pentachoric_decoder_simulation.py
python3 gateaware_decoder_simulation.py
python3 e6_syndrome_decoder_simulation.py
python3 noise_model_decomposition.py
python3 threshold_sweep_simulation.py
python3 pf_gate_simulation.py
python3 native_algorithm_benchmarks.py
```

All scripts use fixed random seeds (`RANDOM_SEED = 42` or equivalent) and produce identical output across platforms. Typical runtime per script: 1–30 minutes on a single CPU core. Peak memory usage: < 4 GB.

